An investigation has been launched after a man was found dead inside a car in Greater Manchester. Police made the grim discovery at 8.45am today. Officers have cordoned off a nearby street while early investigations are carried out. At this stage, police say they do not believe the death is suspicious. Officers were called to the scene due to ‘concern for welfare of a man in a vehicle’ on Boarshaw Road in Middleton, Greater Manchester. The car was reportedly parked near to Middleton Cemetery and Crematorium. Emergency services had rushed to the scene but the 37-year-old man was pronounced dead at the scene. In a statement, Greater Manchester Police said: ‘At around 8:45 today (Saturday 4 March 2023) officers were called to a concern for welfare of a 37-year-old man in a vehicle on Boarshaw Road in Middleton. ‘Emergency services attended, but he was sadly pronounced dead at the scene. ‘Enquiries are ongoing but there are not believed to be any suspicious circumstances surrounding his death.’ Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.